The White House Task Force on Middle Class Families, led by Vice President Joe Biden, held its first meeting in Philadelphia at the University of Pennsylvania. The Task Force's focus is on finding solutions to the economic challenges facing the American middle class, with an emphasis on green jobs. The meeting included cabinet members and members of the Task Force, who discussed the potential of green jobs in creating a strong middle class. The Task Force also released a staff report that highlighted the benefits of green jobs, such as higher pay and unionization. The meeting was transparent and all materials were made available on the Task Force's public website. Panel discussions included experts on green jobs and stakeholders such as governors, mayors, labor leaders, and business representatives.